    <item>
      <title>Monster Weapons Variety</title>
      <author>Logansam</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/558258</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/558258#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">03772578029a0b6bffc18d48cd9d1f8de335a733</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 25 Nov 2024 16:07:17 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6744a055a775b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6744a06b7ab39.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6744a0764d94c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6744a09fb4a62.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;Enemies now hold a greater variety of weapons all throughout Hyrule!&amp;nbsp; Weapons that were once hard to come by - like eightfold longblades - can be won from monsters.&amp;nbsp; And weapons that became totally unobtainable in the vanilla game - kite shields, korok swords, lynel crushers, etc. - are always available somewhere.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The area around a settlement will usually have some monsters carrying that place's equipment.&amp;nbsp; For example, you'll find monsters carrying Zora weapons near the path to Zora's Domain - presumably because they killed traveling Zoras and stole their weapons.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Monsters now hold Sheikah, Zora, Goron, Gerudo, Rito, Korok, and Yiga weapons, as well as double axes and some Lynel weapons.&amp;nbsp; I also changed whether some monsters will rank up or not.&amp;nbsp; There are now three Red, Blue, and White Lynels - one with each weapon type - that will not rank up so you can always fight them and loot their weapons.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Just to clarify, this mod doesn't add any monsters to the map.&amp;nbsp; It just changes existing monsters.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Enjoy!</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/monster_weapons_variety_f74ae_switch.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <category>OverWorld/Field</category>
      <category>Maps</category>
    </item>
